description.3: Kingpin is after the Purple Man after he derailed the Kingpin's six-million dollar heroin deal!
description.8: Heather finds out that her company is doing business with Doc Ock, and Daredevil has to come to her rescue when she is captured. The Widow realizes her relationship with Matt is through and leaves New York.
description.9: Has Johnny Blaze lost his reputation as a stunt man?
description.10: Unlike Frosty, Jack Frost isn't such a jolly, happy soul! He's decided to unleash his minions to attack Hulk...and Doc Samson and General Ross' cabin will be caught in the crossfire!
description.11: Using the martial arts moves taught to him by Captain America, Iron Man battles Titanium Man in Times Square.
description.12: What could Spider-Woman have done to make Spider-Man her enemy!?
description.14: The FF must travel to the North Pole to uncover the source of a worldwide blackout. Who, or what, is behind this villainy?
description.15: Spider-Man must face criminals throughout the city as they battle for complete control of the criminal underworld.
description.17: Thing and the Inhuman Triton dive deep below the surface to face-off against the Serpent Squad!
description.18: Spider-Man and Mockingbird star in a S.H.I.E.L.D.-centric adventure! It's a team-up for the ages, as our two heroes take on Nick Fury's Life Model Decoy, and a sinister plot from the inside of S.H.I.E.L.D. Plus, see Bobbi Morse as Mockingbird for the very first time!
description.19: Will the tensions between Atlantis and Wakanda prevent the Defenders from stopping Mandrill’s latest scheme?
description.20: Staff members at the Daily Bugle have been acting erratically; mood swings are plaguing the office, leaving Peter very confused. What could possibly be behind this rash of insanity? Jonas Harrow and his experimental ray-generator may to blame, but how can Spider-Man stop Harrow when he can't control himself?
description.21: The Avengers experience an unaccustomed period of relaxation between missions. Jocasta is elated at the promise that she will be nominated for team membership. Iron Man decides to step down as chairman. The Beast bribes Wonder Man into a disastrous blind date, and Ms. Marvel visits the Scarlet Witch, who is still on leave. When Ms. Marvel becomes ill, Wanda takes her to a hospital where they are both stunned to learn that she is three months pregnant!
description.22: Baron Strucker strikes! Captain America and Dum Dum Dugan team up to stop the evil super villain before he blows Brooklyn right off the map! Will they succeed? Or will this be Cap's biggest failure? Plus: a startling secret of Captain America revealed.
description.23: Luke Skywalker and Darth Vader enter the dangerous Crystal Valley...will they both walk away?
description.33: Reed Richards links the deformities of the Hydro-Base's inhabitants to the Inhuman's Terrigen Mists!
description.36: Strange returns to the Land of the Living just in time to stop Baron Mordo from sacrificing 12 people!
description.37: Namor returns to Earth after the Tunnelworld adventure only to be greeted by the Black Panther who’s set his sights on the Sub-Mariner! Can peace prevail in this international incident between Atlantis and Wakanda?
description.38: Johnny Blaze is called to defend his records against a new stunt man, but Johnny can't seem to complete any of his stunts!
description.39: Hulk is attacked by the Gardener...who has claimed K'ai's lush terrain for himself! Can our hero and the citizens of K'ai avenge Jarella's death by restoring their homeland to its former glory?
description.40: Addressing a crowd in Times Square, Titanium Man announces that he is going to destroy Manhattan.
description.42: A Spider-Woman imposter is the least of Jessica's problems!
description.44: Susan Storm, Queen of Atlantis? Long has Namor made his affections for the Invisible Girl known, much to the dismay of Reed Richards. But what if Namor and Sue's tense flirtation became a marriage for the ages? As co-rulers of Atlantis, the power couple proves a force to be reckoned with!
description.45: It's a pirate's life for Captain Barracuda- who's stolen the Horn of Atlantis and has big plans for New York City!
description.46: The show must go on! Spider-Man goes against a fashion designer named Belladonna whose weapons are far from pins and sewing needles.
description.47: Darth Vader challenges Luke to a lightsaber duel...will he accept?
description.55: Spider-Man waits for Black Cat to strike at the Hendricks Museum of Musical History. What loot has the Cat set her eyes on now? And when she and Spider-Man battle it out, will Black Cat bare her fangs? Peter discovers that new girlfriend Dawn Starr has ulterior motives.
description.56: How does Taskmaster fit into the strange events at the Solomon Institute? Will the Avengers be able to save Wasp from twisted experimentation at the hands of "Solomon"?
description.57: He was just a guy named Joe until society stole his son. Now, he's back, and he may just be Caps deadliest foe yet!
description.58: Two underground enemies emerge during the 1980 Winter Olympics and wreak havoc! Luckily, Spider-Man is on the scene to stop them, but when Kala and her Lava Men add the Incredible Hulk to their team, the competition gets fierce!
description.64: Hellcat and Valkyrie make a discovery about Hellcat’s powers while they stop a bank robbery. In Tunnelworld, Doctor Strange must use his mystic abilities to battle for the Hulk's mind!
description.65: What happens when Ben Urich discovers that Matt Murdock is the sightless adventurer Daredevil?!
description.66: Johnny is in a race against time to rejoin with the Ghost Rider Spirit!
description.67: Hulk and the citizens of K'ai mourn the loss of Queen Jarella.
description.68: After Justin Hammer remotely compromised the Iron Man armor, Tony vowed to never let something like that happen again. Now, he must test his armor to be sure.
description.70: Things get tricky when Spider-Woman saves a newspaper tycoon!
description.72: Six Hellfire Club troops against lil' ol' Wolverine? The Hellfire goons never stood a chance. And John Byrne's rendition of this scene makes that perfectly clear, almost to the point where you expect Wolvie to leap off the cover and slash you!
description.73: Peter's night out with ESU classmates becomes a dizzying battle against the Frightful Four! Will Spider-Man ever catch a break? Plus, Electro pulls the wool over Spidey's eyes- by posing as the Human Torch!
description.79: Darth Vader learns who it was who destroyed the Death Star...and now he plans his revenge!
description.80: Black Cat is leaving her calling card for Spider-Man at the Guggenheim Museum. With her attempted, and repeated, theft of the Golden Lovers statue, it seems that Cat is back in action! But when Black Cat pays two cents for the $4 million dollar 'Rajah Ruby' at an auction, Spider-Man can't let her walk. Plus, Peter goes on a blind date!
description.81: The Avengers break into the Solomon Institute for the Criminally Insane to locate missing team member Wasp. Selbe is revealed to be a clone of "Solomon", the head "doctor" of the institute. Solomon's intentions with Selbe however, are far from benevolent.
description.82: When a survivor of the Holocaust seeks revenge on a former Nazi, will Captain America be able to stop her from making the biggest mistake of her life? Don't miss the Calypso connection!
description.85: Black Panther at last discovers the secrets he's been searching for, and an unsolved mystery is finally revealed! With these new facts, T'Challa decides the time for searching is over, and the time for action is NOW!
description.88: Johnny Blaze is finally free of the Ghost Rider, but without Johnny to reign in the Rider, Hell will break loose!
description.89: In a failed attempt to help the Hulk, Captain Marvel accidentally shrinks the Green Goliath to subatomic size!
description.90: A badly damaged Iron Man must help Bruce Banner before it's too late.
description.91: Spider-Woman takes on the Doomsday Room, the deranged playground of the Gamesman! Plus, who is this "clone" of Jessica Drew?!
description.93: We know Rick Jones was the hero of the Kree-Skrull war, but what if he was killed before humanity's salvation? Ronan the Accuser takes matters into his own hands, and the Avengers are left defenseless!
description.94: It is revealed that HERBIE is controlled by the intelligence of Dr. Sun...and he has Mister Fantastic, Invisible Girl and Thing under siege in the Baxter Building!
description.95: Spider-Man and Giant Man team up to take down Meteor Man!
description.97: Pledging allegiance to Baron Mordo, Julian Phyffe and Strange have a fight that ends with Phyffe dying in a car crash. But that's not quite the end of Phyffe...
description.98: The Hulk is being mind-controlled by an evil wizard! Can the Sorcerer Supreme save Hulk before it’s too late for both of them?

2.text: A bomb has gone off inside the Gem Theater, and the Heroes for Hire must hunt down the culprits! But the men responsible may have a few tricks up their sleeves; will Power Man and Iron Fist lose the Last Gamble?

3.text: Kingpin is after the Purple Man after he derailed the Kingpin's six-million dollar heroin deal!

4.text: Pamela Quinn may be in grave danger at the hands of the Satan Squad! Will Machine Man uncover Baron Brimstone's plot…and stay intact?

6.text: DARK PHOENIX! Jean Grey has become the Dark Phoenix, a corruption of the cosmic entity bonded to Jean. Now the Dark Phoenix seeks to destroy everything in its path! What can the X-Men do to defeat it? Must they kill Jean Grey?

7.text: She-Hulk is tired of people like Tony Stark pushing her around…time to teach him a lesson!

24.text: TEARS FOR THE WORLD CALLED HEAVEN Star-Lord travels to a world beyond the Stars, a world called Heaven—a world of no return!

26.text: Pirates have ruined Barbie Bannister’s life, and only Man-Thing can protect this damsel-in-distress from further harm!

27.text: Upon the defeat of his evil father Fu Manchu, Shang-Chi parts ways with his crew and heads for Chinatown.

30.text: TOO LATE, THE HEROES! Cyclops has survived! The X-Men retaliate against the Hellfire club-this time, with the power of the Phoenix on their side. But not everything is as it seems with Jean. Enter: Dark Phoenix!

31.text: She-Hulk must hold a bridge together after a raging earthquake!

32.text: The Red Skull in possession of the Cosmic Cube! Trouble awaits humanity as Marvel's most dastardly villain harnesses raw, universal power. Will S.H.I.E.L.D. be able to land their retrieval mission for the dangerous artifact? And what happens if they fail?

48.text: After Power Man and Iron Fist put a stop to a number of Señor Suerte’s gambling rings, the Señor demands revenge! Power Man learns about a bomb planted in the Gem Theater. Time is ticking for the Heroes for Hire!

49.text: Featuring two FANTASTIC guest-stars – the Thing and Human Torch! Ion's uncontrolled rage leads her to seek answers from the wrong folks…and Machine Man steps in to deliver justice!

50.text: Shang-Chi has one last showdown with his father as he chases after Fu Manchu's flying saucer.

60.text: Sheriff Morris Walters fights She-Hulk not knowing that she is his own flesh and blood…in fact, his daughter!

61.text: The fate of Adam Warlock will be revealed at last!

63.text: Peter Parker bumps into Jack Russell while in Los Angeles on assignment for the Globe! But when the evil Tatterdemalion targets a room full of people, will they risk their secret identities to help?

72.text: WOLVERINE ALONE! Cyclops desperately tries to reach out Jean and bring her out of her dark transformation. But Mastermind has other plans and attacks Cyclops on the astral plane! Can Scott survive death in this psychic realm?

Six Hellfire Club troops against lil' ol' Wolverine? The Hellfire goons never stood a chance. And John Byrne's rendition of this scene makes that perfectly clear, almost to the point where you expect Wolvie to leap off the cover and slash you!

75.text: Guest-starring Doctor Strange! While investigating some mysterious disappearances in Citrusville, the Sorcerer Supreme conflicts with Man-Thing! And Baron Mordo lies in wait…

76.text: Fu Manchu unleashes the warrior Maru against his own son!

83.text: Thing and Starhawk track Moondragon and Her to the High Evolutionary's Counter-Earth. There they clash over the absconded Alicia Masters.

85.text: Black Panther at last discovers the secrets he's been searching for, and an unsolved mystery is finally revealed! With these new facts, T'Challa decides the time for searching is over, and the time for action is NOW!

86.text: AND HELLFIRE IS THEIR NAME! Using Angel's Hellfire Club membership, the X-Men infiltrate a club event, only to be met with extreme force. Can the X-Men survive this battle? Will Jean finally become the Black Queen?

87.text: Jennifer Walters needs a lawyer! She-Hulk has been framed for a murder she didn’t commit!

99.text: Fah Lo Suee tries to build a coalition of heroes to fight Fu Manchu.
